---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="The Woods"
  description="Gledhow Valley Woods — a 57-acre urban woodland in north Leeds. Discover the ecology, history, and conservation projects in this remarkable green space."
  section="the-woods"
>
  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <section class="bg-forest-800 text-white py-16 md:py-24 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img src="/images/PXL_20240430_170751404.jpg" alt="Tall beech trees lining a path through Gledhow Valley Woods" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-forest-900/70"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <p class="text-forest-200 font-sans text-sm uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Gledhow Valley Woods</p>
      <h1 class="font-heading font-bold text-5xl md:text-7xl text-white mb-6">The Woods</h1>
      <p class="font-body text-cream-200 text-xl max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        A ribbon of ancient woodland and grassland running 1.5 km through north Leeds — home to 115 species of birds,
        186 species of plants, 74 species of fungi, and 14 species of butterflies.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SECTION NAVIGATION -->
  <nav class="bg-white border-b border-cream-400 sticky top-16 md:top-20 z-40" aria-label="Woods section navigation">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex overflow-x-auto gap-0 py-0">
        {[
          { label: 'About the Woods', href: '/the-woods/about' },
          { label: 'Projects',        href: '/the-woods/projects' },
          { label: 'History of the Woods', href: '/the-woods/history' },
          { label: 'Gledhow Valley Road', href: '/the-woods/gledhow-valley-road' },
          { label: 'Flora & Fauna',   href: '/the-woods/flora-fauna' },
        ].map(item => (
          <a
            href={item.href}
            class="shrink-0 px-4 py-3 text-sm font-sans font-medium text-forest-700 border-b-2 border-transparent hover:border-forest-600 hover:text-forest-900 transition-colors whitespace-nowrap"
          >
            {item.label}
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- INTRO CONTENT -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-start">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-forest-900 text-3xl md:text-4xl mb-5">A woodland in the city</h2>
        <div class="prose prose-lg font-body text-earth-800">
          <p>
            Gledhow Valley Woods occupies a glacially formed valley carved by meltwater during the last ice age. Its steep, wooded sides and the stream at its floor — Gledhow Beck — give it a naturally secluded character that makes it a remarkable urban nature reserve in the heart of north Leeds.
          </p>
          <p>
            The 57-acre site is designated as a Conservation Area and is part of the wider Gledhow Valley Conservation Area, designated by Leeds City Council in December 2006. The valley contains significant listed buildings including the Grade II* Gledhow Hall and the Grade II Gipton Spa Bath House (1671).
          </p>
          <p>
            The woods were given to Leeds Corporation in 1944 by the Hon. Hilda Kitson, ensuring their permanent protection as a public open space.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <!-- Stats -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
          {[
            { value: '57',  unit: 'acres',    label: 'of woodland and grassland' },
            { value: '115', unit: 'species',  label: 'of birds recorded' },
            { value: '186', unit: 'species',  label: 'of plants recorded' },
            { value: '1996', unit: '',        label: 'FGVW founded' },
          ].map(s => (
            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-4 border border-cream-400 shadow-sm text-center">
              <div class="font-heading font-bold text-forest-700 text-4xl leading-none">{s.value}</div>
              {s.unit && <div class="text-sm font-sans text-forest-600 font-medium">{s.unit}</div>}
              <div class="text-xs font-sans text-earth-500 mt-1">{s.label}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg h-48 overflow-hidden">
          <img src="/images/PXL_20240705_062852566.jpg" alt="The pond at Gledhow Valley Woods with summer meadow flowers" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SUB-SECTION CARDS -->
  <section class="bg-bluebell-50 py-14">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="font-heading font-bold text-forest-900 text-3xl mb-8">Explore further</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5">
        {[
          { title: 'About the Woods',      href: '/the-woods/about',              desc: 'The valley, its ecology, and what makes Gledhow Valley Woods special.' },
          { title: 'Projects & Improvements', href: '/the-woods/projects',        desc: 'Current and past conservation and improvement projects.' },
          { title: 'History of the Woods', href: '/the-woods/history',            desc: 'How the woods came to be — from the glacial age to the present day.' },
          { title: 'Gledhow Valley Road',  href: '/the-woods/gledhow-valley-road', desc: 'A detailed historical record of the road opened in 1926.' },
          { title: 'Flora & Fauna',        href: '/the-woods/flora-fauna',        desc: 'The remarkable diversity of wildlife in this urban nature reserve.' },
        ].map(card => (
          <a href={card.href} class="group bg-white rounded-lg p-5 border border-cream-400 shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-shadow">
            <h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-forest-800 text-xl mb-2 group-hover:text-forest-600 transition-colors">{card.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-earth-600 text-sm font-body leading-relaxed">{card.desc}</p>
            <span class="mt-3 inline-block text-sm font-sans font-semibold text-forest-700 group-hover:underline">Read more →</span>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
